The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT) and specifically focuses on incentive compatibility and revenue maximization (cs.EC). The use of budgets and payments also suggests a connection to distributed systems (cs.DS) and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper mentions a revenue equivalence theorem, which is a concept from information theory (cs.IT).
